<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Alle:
[B]Welcome to the "Lord of the Flies" aka EverQuest.  Justice is in the hands of the stronger.

EQ today.  At higher levels where everyone is competing for rare spawns (like ragefire), EQ has degenerated into humanity at it lowest levels.  A rare spawn appears and it dies within minutes, often accompanied by angry accusations that you stole this from my guild/group.  The high level content and rare spawns is a classic example of EQ at it's uggliest.  

Now otherwise good people are turning EQ into something akin to road rage.  Put them into the EQ world and things they would normally never consider doing suddenly  become perfectly rational behavior.

I used to spend a large portion of my time helping others.  I would travel across multiple zones to rez someone because I got some sad story.  When newbies asked for buffs, I would gladly accomodate.  I was happy to take the time to show people where things were when asked.   LOL, I even used to wander around newbie areas and cast Resolution on complete strangers just for the joy it gave them. 

Alas, this "Lord of the Flies" attitude is beginning to affect me also.  Nowdays, I won't travel anywhere to help anyone but a good friend or a guildmate.  I have changed my tag to /roleplay so strangers can't easily locate me.  I ignore the newbies asking for buffs.  I rarely even play my cleric anymore as I am so disgusted with the high end EQ game.  

All of us pay the same amount to play EQ.  As such, we should all have an equal right to enjoy the game whether we are with a small group of friends or a large guild.  We shouldn't have to pack up and leave an area because a larger, better organized guild has announced that they are taking over the spawn and are better equiped to kill it than we are.  Stop and think of how our world would be if this was common practice.  If someone stronger than you wants your house/car/freedom/etc. they can just come and take it away?  What you say?  This is only a game so this logic doesn't apply?  Think again my friend.  Ask yourself "What would you do if you could do anything you wanted to and no one could prevent you from doing it or even know who you really were?"  Are you sure we aren't seeing this actually happen in Everquest?

Welcome to EverQuest.  Your in our world now.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
